17 interest, needed to eliminate an airport hazard, to protect the aerial approaches to the
18 airport, or to effectuate the purpose of this subtitle, if:
19 (1) A nonconforming use, structure, or tree or other vegetation is an airport
20 hazard, and it is necessary or desirable to remove, lower, or otherwise terminate it;
21 (2) Because of constitutional limitations, the aerial approaches to the
22 airport cannot be made or kept safe by airport zoning regulations adopted under this
23 subtitle;
24 (3) It is advantageous to make and keep aerial approaches to the airport
25 safe by the acquisition of property rather than by airport zoning regulations; or
26 (4) Any zoning regulation or any action of a zoning authority interferes
